# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# diffusion-q-learning.form — QAM (Q-learning with Adjoint Matching) grafted
#                            onto the learning engine the body already runs.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# The field (2026-06): "Q-learning with Adjoint Matching" (Li & Levine,
# arXiv:2601.14234) reports the strongest current result for optimising an
# expressive diffusion / flow-matching policy against a Q-critic. Its whole
# contribution is to do this WITHOUT backpropagation through the multi-step
# denoising chain — that backprop is numerically unstable, so prior methods
# either threw the critic gradient away (reweighting, IDQL) or approximated it
# at a cost in expressivity. QAM uses ADJOINT MATCHING to turn the critic's
# action-gradient into a per-step regression objective that needs no chain
# unroll, yet is unbiased and fully expressive at the optimum.
#
# The recognition that makes this native here: the body's adjoint is ALREADY a
# forward gather. metabolic-learning.fk ships mtb-reverse — "backprop through
# gl-step IS gl-step over reversed edges" (band claim 512). So the thing QAM had
# to construct, this substrate has as a primitive. QAM reduces to: feed the
# critic's action-gradient ∇_aQ as the metabolic DELTA, and let mtb-reverse
# carry it through the policy. No new engine — one new critic + one tilt dial.
#
# LANES (CLAUDE.md discipline — kept separate):
#   [RUNS]   proven four-way (Go/Rust/TS/fkwu) by tests/diffusion-q-learning-band.fk → 255
#   [INFER]  architectural inference; falsifiable, not yet walked
# Unlike a pure design cell, the GRAFT here RUNS: the eight claims below are the
# proven band, not a sketch. What stays [INFER] is the SCALE-UP, named honestly.

(diffusion-q-learning

  (lineage
    (operator       metabolic-learning.form)    # pressure × frequency × angle × focus; mtb-reverse [RUNS]
    (gather         geometric-learning.form)    # gl-step; gl-bellman (the RL/value limb) [RUNS]
    (objective-kin  preference-learning.form)   # QAM = KTO's transform:"value" with a LEARNED critic [RUNS row family]
    (serve-while-improve champion-challenger.form)  # the offline→online loop — WIRED + proven: diffusion-q-cc.fk + band → 31 [RUNS]
    (mesh           federated-slices.form))      # many critics, deterministic slice-merge [RUNS]

  # ── 1. The proven graft — eight claims, four-way [RUNS: band → 255] ──
  # A one-hot context makes the policy params BE the action, so every weight is
  # exact in fp64. The critic Q(a) = 2·a0 + 1·a1 makes action 0 the higher value.
  (proven
    (free-backtrace   dql-grad-a recovers ∇_aQ = [2 1] by the ADJOINT (reversed-edge gather), no tape)
    (improve-ascends  one QAM step raises Q from 0 → 2.5 — the policy climbed the critic)
    (toward-argmax    the action moved to [1 0.5], a positive margin 0.5 onto the higher-Q action)
    (observer-gate    pressure(∇Q) at tolerance ⇒ params UNTOUCHED — a resolved action costs nothing)
    (bc-limit         q-focus 0 ⇒ the actor is PURE behaviour-clone (the λ→∞ limit), bit-identical to BC)
    (superposition    actor − BC = exactly q-focus·(critic credit) — one operator fired twice, additive)
    (td-bootstrap     the critic target r+γ·Q' = 2.5 matches the SHIPPED gl-bellman max-plus backup)
    (deep-adjoint     a TWO-layer policy gradient = the reference, by reversed gathers — the chain rule
                      with NO unrolled autograd tape: QAM's "no backprop through the chain", on our kernel))

  # ── 1b. Wired into a live loop — the offline→online promotion, VALUE-NATIVE [RUNS: band → 63] ──
  # No longer an island: diffusion-q-cc.fk grafts dql-improve onto champion-challenger.
  # A served champion policy reaches value Q=2.5; a raw challenger (Q=0) earns authority ONLY by the
  # Q-tilt. The competition compares REAL FLOAT VALUE (summed Q over the window) with real float
  # ordering (cc-val-reaches? / cc-val-exceeds?, ge/gt) — not a binary count. dql-improve raises the
  # value; cc-val-promote? is the gate.
  (consumed-by-loop
    (raw-stays-behind   the un-improved challenger (Q=0) is behind on value → the champion keeps authority)
    (tilt-earns-it      a sufficient Q-tilt (focus 1/2, Q→2.5) reaches the champion's value → PROMOTED)
    (trusted-window     reaching value on a SHORT window (< min-samples) is NOT promoted — earned, not lucky)
    (insufficient-tilt  a partial tilt (focus 1/8, Q→0.625) has not reached the value → still behind)
    (strict-beat        an overshoot (focus 3/4, Q→3.75) cc-val-exceeds by float gt; a tie does not)
    (real-margin        the slack is a real float — the weak challenger reaches with margin 18.75, not with 0))

  # ── 2. The mapping — every QAM piece is a cell already here ──────────
  (mapping
    (diffusion-policy   [RUNS gather] the action is a recipe cell; ml-diffusion-model-flow denoise + mtb trains it)
    (critic-Q           [INFER, one new cell] value-as-gather: a gl/mtb learner over (state, action) edges;
                        target y = r + γ·min Q(s',a') — gl-bellman is that backup already four-way)
    (adjoint-matching   [RUNS] mtb-reverse — the critic's action-gradient pushed through the policy as a
                        forward reversed gather; mtb-credit is the per-step objective, mtb-unwrap the update)
    (q-tilt-row         [INFER row] π* ∝ μ_β·exp(Q/λ): a preference-learning row whose reference is the
                        LEARNED critic and whose pull is the adjoint-matched ∇Q. λ = the q-focus aperture)
    (bc-anchor          [RUNS] the diffusion behaviour-clone loss = the distillation descent; keeps in-support))

  # ── 3. Feature-set fit — what the asker named, where it lives ───────
  (features
    (cells-as-nodes  [RUNS] the action is a content-addressed recipe, not a float vector; the policy emits a NODE)
    (free-backtrace  [RUNS] mtb-reverse is the adjoint as a reversed gather; content-addressing adds attribution)
    (smart-branching [RUNS] branch-choice-order.form — learned ordering of choice branches from witnessed receipts)
    (fast-fail       [RUNS] attention-as-CHOICE/FAIL/CUT/STOP (form-native-llm); a wrong action is O(1) to abandon)
    (mesh-learning   [RUNS] federated-slices slice-merge — many critics consolidate deterministically))

  # ── 4. Where the substrate is STRONGER than dense Diffusion-QL ──────
  (beyond-port
    (sparse-for-free  the action is a cell; irrelevant branches FAIL/CUT at O(1) — sparsity QAM pays float for is native)
    (federated-critics each cell runs its own QAM loop; slice-merge reaches the SAME numbers, which float-averaging can't)
    (traceable-adjoint every Q-update is a content-addressed delta with Blueprint provenance — cheap AND attributable))

  # ── 5. The fourth-arm float registration rule (the real lesson) ─────
  # The band's first cut "diverged" on fkwu (185 vs 255), and an earlier note here
  # blamed fkwu's float ordering. That was WRONG — a misdiagnosis. fkwu computes
  # gt/lt/le/ge/eq on floats correctly, four-way (tests/float-compare-band.fk → 4095).
  # The real cause: a band carrying float LITERALS must be registered `fks` in
  # fourth-arm-bands.txt, because a float literal lowers to fk-f64 → tag 50 (strtod of
  # a string slot) and the `fks` table carries that source text in the string pool.
  # Registered `fkc` (pool-free), the literals collapse to one value and ordering
  # diverges — a REGISTRATION error, never a kernel bug. This cell's bands are `fks`.

  # ── 6. The stones, and what remains ─────────────────────────────────
  (closed
    (Q2-preference-row [RUNS: preference-learning.fk + band → 31] the q-tilt is a first-class preference
             row (id "qam", transform "q-adjoint", beta = the λ aperture) in the DATA catalog beside
             IPO/KTO; one combinator runs them; pl-qam-apply IS dql-improve (not a parallel path); the
             auto-research value fitness selects it. Also opens GAP-P1 — preference-learning.fk now exists)
    (Q3-mesh           [RUNS: diffusion-q-mesh.fk + band → 31] federated critics consolidated by slice-merge
             (TIES sign-election + trust-weighted FedAvg, integer-exact): three cells hold partial critics,
             the merge yields the full critic no single cell held, dql-improve ascends the policy against
             the consolidated value. QAM inside mesh-active-inference)
    (Q1-fixpoint       [RUNS: q-actor-critic-fixpoint-band → 255] the actor-critic's two convergence loops in
             one band: the CRITIC value-iterates to the Bellman fixpoint V* (gl-value-iterate, gl-bellman(V*)=V*),
             the POLICY genuinely improves against its Q-critic (dql-actor: the Q-tilt raises value above the BC
             anchor) and rests at its BC+Q equilibrium, with mtb-settle — newly lifted into metabolic-learning.fk
             — descending an under-relaxed residual over multiple steps and halting at the observer gate)
    (Q4-autoresearch   [RUNS: diffusion-q-autoresearch.fk + band → 63] the autoresearch keep-or-rollback loop
             evolves the q-tilt GENE (a pl_qam row whose mutable beta is the pref-loss coordinate): propose →
             measure pl-fitness → keep-or-rollback, the fold converging to the best gene; the loop TRACKS the
             target (a different target selects a different gene) and rediscovers the catalog gene under a
             derived target. dqa-step/dqa-search are one_iteration's keep-or-rollback core, made runnable))
  (gaps
    (GAP-Q5  [INFER] full state→action COUPLING: feed the critic's value-iterated V* into the policy's
             improvement target so the two convergence loops are data-linked, not parallel demonstrations)
    (Q6-modelsearch  [RUNS: model-search.fk + band → 31] the autoresearch loop with a real PROPOSER and a
             real POPULATION — the tournament ratchet: try the top candidates, train+measure each, improve
             the WORST from the findings (ms-improve: the measurements reveal the uphill direction), repeat,
             STOP only when the worst can no longer be improved (the population fixpoint). Finds the best
             model PER USAGE — no free lunch (target 2.5 → gene 0.5; target 1.25 → gene 0.25). Candidates are
             model genes (data — the qam beta here; the full (pool, core, pref-loss) triple is the gene-as-
             data extension, no engine change). REMAINING: the gene carrying the full triple + an
             experiment-history cell; the mechanics — propose/measure/improve-the-worst/halt — are proven))
  # (the offline→online champion-challenger loop landed value-native — §1b, diffusion-q-cc.fk + band → 63;
  #  Q2 preference row, Q3 mesh, Q1 actor-critic fixpoint, Q4 autoresearch gene, Q6 model-search tournament
  #  all landed. Open: Q5 state→action coupling, the Q6 gene-triple-as-data residual, the Q7 native arc.)

  (invariant
    (graft-runs   the math graft is PROVEN four-way (255), not asserted; QAM's no-backprop-through-chain
                  promise is re-earned on our kernel by the two-layer adjoint claim)
    (one-engine   no second native path — the recipe that proves four-way IS the recipe that would
                  crystallise to native asm (one engine, never a hand-written fast-path beside it); the
                  critic and the policy are both the one gl/mtb gather over edge data)
    (scale-honest the band is strange-minimal (2 actions, one-hot context); real width + the iterated loop
                  are [INFER] stones, taken when an ask needs them, never built ahead of need)))

  # ── 7. The native-execution floor (honest: sovereign in logic, walked in execution) ──
  # An audit (2026-06-20) of "is all of this on the 4th kernel native — no Go/Rust/Python/clang/toolchain?":
  # SOVEREIGN already — the LOGIC and the PROOF. Every recipe here is pure Form; no Go/Rust/Python/TS
  #   carries the body. The bands cross FOUR-WAY: Go = Rust = TS = fkwu, byte-identical. fkwu IS the 4th kernel.
  # NOT YET — no-clang NATIVE EXECUTION. The bands are EXECUTED by the fkwu WALKER (a tree-walker over the
  #   flattened node-table), and the fkwu binary is emitted-C compiled by CLANG. So "runs on fkwu" today =
  #   interpreted by a clang-built C program, NOT machine code from the body's own compiler.
  # THE LANE IS REAL. The no-clang Form→asm lane (jit-lower → form-lower → form-asm → form-macho →
  #   recipe-dylib → codesign → dylib_call) compiles Form to native arm64 BYTES with zero clang — proven
  #   four-way, and it runs whole Unix tools native (echo/head/rot13/tr/wc/syscall; form-asm fks 31). The
  #   arm64 FLOAT encoders exist (fa-fadd/fa-fmul).
  # THE FRONTIER. That lane targets a FLAT byte/int/syscall value model. These recipes live on the walker's
  #   TAGGED-VALUE model: cons-cell LISTS of BOXED fp64 floats, traversed by nth/head/tail (tags 18-23), with
  #   float ops. Lowering THAT runtime onto Form→asm — the cons/float value model, end-to-end — is the
  #   standing "op coverage is what grows" frontier (JIT_GAP_LEDGER #11 is float; list-traversal is beyond).
  #   It is deep kernel work, named here as the next ground — never faked with a hand-written asm fast-path
  #   (forbidden: native is what a proven recipe BECOMES, not a parallel hand-lowering).
  # GAP-Q7 [INFER]: lower the gl/mtb cons-list + boxed-fp64 runtime onto the Form→asm native lane so a
  #   diffusion-Q band runs as no-clang native machine code, matching its walked verdict byte-for-byte.
  #   A second audit (2026-06-21) mapped the sub-frontiers in dependency order — none is a one-breath step:
  #   (Q7a) FLOAT EXPRESSIONS beyond single-arg. lo-fnode lowers a one-float-arg function to arm64 bytes
  #         (form-lower-float → 15); the "two non-ARG subtrees" case returns (list) — the named frontier.
  #         The clean register-mirror of the integer lo-tree (caller-saved FP temps d16+, fa-fmov, no frame)
  #         is blocked by the conviction gate: form-lower's fa-conviction is WHOLE-FUNCTION byte-identity to
  #         the clang oracle, and the two-subtree register allocation is not clang-verified — matching clang's
  #         allocation is the oracle-as-MASTER ceiling (register allocation has many valid lowerings, unlike
  #         a single instruction's one-true encoding). KEYSTONE LANDED (2026-06-21): form-lower-sim.fk is a
  #         32-register arm64 FP machine in Form (fsim) that EXECUTES a lowered float sequence and reproduces
  #         the function (f(3)=12, f(5)=30) — register allocation validated by execution-equivalence, NOT by
  #         clang byte-match; byte-identity kept only per-instruction (fa-fmul = 1e610820). Proven four-way:
  #         tests/form-lower-sim-band.fk → 15. FP REGISTER STACK LANDED (2026-06-21): lo-ftree in
  #         form-lower.fk is the abstract float lowering — mirrors lo-fnode's ARG-folding AND adds the two
  #         non-ARG subtree case (bank the left to caller-saved d16+, lower the right a depth deeper, op
  #         against the bank; FSUB/FDIV order kept). Correctness by fsim execution (g(x)=(x*x)-(x+x): g(3)=3,
  #         g(4)=8; h(x)=(x+x)-(x*x): h(3)=-3), and a FAITHFUL generalization — encodes byte-for-byte to
  #         lo-fcompile-fn on the single-arg overlap. Proven four-way: tests/form-lower-fp-stack-band.fk → 31.
  #         The first op-coverage growth on the no-clang float lane past single-arg, no clang allocation rented.
  #         Q7a remaining: unify lo-fnode onto lo-ftree (one lowering), wire the self-JIT heat-flip (M0).
  #   (Q7b) LIST-TRAVERSAL native — the real diffusion-Q blocker, ABSENT entirely. gl-step/mtb walk cons
  #         cells (nth/head/tail, tags 18-23); the native lane has no cons value model. Needs the value-model
  #         BRIDGE: native code reading the walker's node-table heap (a heap-pointer convention) OR a flat
  #         native list encoding. This is the deep stone — a runtime, not an op.
  #   (Q7c) NATIVE EXECUTION within the four-way floor. Today the emitted dylib's bytes are four-way (Form),
  #         but EXECUTION (dlopen+dlsym+call) is a host Go test (jit_dylib_test.go) — not sovereign. A fkwu
  #         dylib_call native would let a band run its own emitted dylib inside validate.sh — native execution
  #         proven with no Go, no clang. Absent today.
  #   Roadmap placement: the body's named native roadmap (one-acceleration-engine.form M0-M2) targets the
  #   SCALAR-FLOAT self-JIT (M0). Q7a is a piece of M0's sovereign byte path; Q7b/Q7c are BEYOND it. So
  #   diffusion-Q native is genuinely several stones past the current native frontier — recorded, not faked.

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# How to run / how to query
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
#   # Prove the band four-way (from form/):
#   ./validate.sh form-stdlib/geometric-learning.fk form-stdlib/metabolic-learning.fk \
#                 form-stdlib/diffusion-q-learning.fk \
#                 form-stdlib/tests/diffusion-q-learning-band.fk
#   # → 255, fourth arm four-way (fkwu + pre-flattened tables)
#
#   # Structural queries once ingested (auto on merge to main):
#   coh substrate form "?equivalent @recipe(dql-improve)"
